	   <tr><td colspan=2>A horse? For a bard? That's like giving swim fins to marathon runner.&nbsp;&nbsp;A bard with Selo's and a magic drum can outrun any horse.  Horse have to build up speed and then gradually slow down. Bards instantly move at max speed and stop on a dime.  Only the fastest horses, after building up to top speed, can come close to a bard with Selo's and Drums of the Beast.  <br><br>The big advantage for casters is that they can sit and meditate on a horse and still cast spells. For them a horse makes sense.  Since bard meditate caps at 1 you are better off putting the money into getting a Flowing Thought item.  <br>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
