	   <a name=105372813038001></a>
	   <form action=http://www1.allakhazam.com/perl/strategy/mrate.pl name=f105372813038001><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=4&mid=105372813038001>RE: Just starting out...</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=4&mid=105372813038001#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=158164><span id=Scholar>Lucifugeevil</span></a>, <span id=Scholar>Scholar</span><br><span id=notbold>19 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Fri, May 23rd 6:57 PM 2003</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent<span id=notbold>[3.22]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>Q: Is the choice of deity important?<br>A: Deity choice only allows you to wear restricted armor for the additional stat which is usually something like Wisdom so not very important.&nbsp;&nbsp;Chosing a deity will make all illusion masks effectively worthless to you since the deity faction will have a stronger effect than anything else you can do.  I still remember getting the DE Illusion mask and going to the OT Fort to immediately catch a 950 HT from the named SK in there due to having a good aligned diety.<br><br>The only real effects from race are Humans have no night vision, Vah Shir need large armoe, Humans and Half-Elfs wear medium armor and Wood-Elves can wear small or medium armor.  That is it other than stats.<br><br>There are no xp penaties to note.  High end gear equals out all stats and is usually not race dependent so go with what you like.  Check out all of the diety specific cultural gear that you like and chose accordingly if you chose not to go with Agnostic which I would recommend unless you really want that extra stat from it.  The good stuff has level restrictions anyway so there ya go.  I would focus on the Dex and the Charisma.  All high end gear has strength and you cannot avoid getting it high anyway so don't worry so much about it.  Stamina is the hardest to get up in gear while getting the other key stats up and there is not a lot of high Charisma melee gear.  The extra Dex will also help with weapon procs since that is a large source of melee damage for a bard since we are weak melee'ers till high level and still weak there compared to others.<br>&nbsp;<br>It's never too late to give up all hope...</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 >&nbsp;</td><td align=right valign=bottom>
	   <span style='font-weight: normal; font-size: 9px;'>[<a href=#top>Top</a>]</span></tr>
