<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%>
	   <a name=105360821627884></a>
	   <form action=http://www1.allakhazam.com/perl/strategy/mrate.pl name=f105360821627884><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=4&mid=105360821627884>RE: Just starting out...</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=4&mid=105360821627884#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=61546><span id=Sage>Slipskin</span></a>, <span id=Sage>Sage</span><br><span id=notbold>847 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Thu, May 22nd 9:38 AM 2003</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Good<span id=notbold>[3.66]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>So many questions and no easy answers.&nbsp;&nbsp;The first thing to think about is how do you plan to play your bard?  Will the emphasis be on magic or melee or about an even split?  Personally, I tend to melee a lot but have been known to play the ghetto enchanter from time to time.<br><br>None of the races open for bards have any major experience penalties so don't concern yourself about that.<br><br>The main stats for a bard are DEX, CHA, STR, and (as with any class) STA.  DEX helps you learn melee skills faster and reduces the frequency of missed notes (the bard equivelent of a spell fizzle).  CHA helps with charm songs and also with reducing the chance a mob will aggro on you after a failed harmonize.  STR is needed since bards do get to wear plate armor and carry most melee weapons (no 2 handers but thats about it). STA affects the amount of HP you get and how fast you fatigue during combat, jumping, and swimming. INT plays a factor in the mid to high end games since a few of the bard songs actually do use mana. Don't lose sleep over it though.<br><br>Deity is not important unless you plan on wearing deity specific armors.  The downside of having a deity is that it will limit places you can travel to, even with illusions.  <br><br>Which race you choose doesn't really matter much with bards.  Humans can't see in the dark. That's about the only downside I can think of. Very easy to offset with simple gear. Bards are so versitile that the race factor just doesn't affect the class performance much at all.  Vah Shir are slightly better at melee due to the high starting STR.  Wood Elves are slightly better on the defensive skills.  Early on this makes some difference but in the high end game your gear and songs will more than make up for any minor deficiencies.  Go with what looks cool to you.<br>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 >&nbsp;</td><td align=right valign=bottom>
	   <span style='font-weight: normal; font-size: 9px;'>[<a href=#top>Top</a>]</span></tr>
