	   <tr><td colspan=2>For great guides, have a look at eqdiva.com&nbsp;&nbsp; They have guides to all the kite techniques, Fear, Charm, Chant and swarm (if there are more please fell free to add to this).<br><br>Basiclly swarmming is you pull a load of mobs, charm one of em, get all the others to attack the charmed one, watch its hp bar and when it is low break the charm (invis song and dong foget the wind instrument required), and then finish the mob off with chant songs. Then start again with another from the group.<br><br>I was pulling the whole spectre island in Oasis of Marr at lvl 40 with this technique, getting gasps of amazement from a lvl 48 Paladin, who was struggling with 1 spectre at a time, which for me summs up the power of a soloing Bard.<br><br>At 27 I was fear kiteing the most effective as we dont get chant song till lvl 30. Best place I found for this was Lake of Ill Omen around the zone entrance with Frontier Mountains.  Great technique to max out weapon skills as well as once you start to Swarm, well i didnt hit a mob for about 15 levels in all.<br><br>Hope this helps a little. But eqdiva.com will reveal all<br>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
