	   <tr><td colspan=2>Who said bards are not any good at soloing?&nbsp;&nbsp;They're have never played a bard (at least not to any reasonable level). Bards can kite as good as any druid or wizard.  It just requires busier finger work on the keyboard.  <br><br>Bards get track skill at level 35. Not as good as a ranger but good enough for most folks needs.<br><br>When grouped, bards have a different job than rangers.  The bard's job is to fill in for whatever else is missing or to enhance the existing capabilities of the group.  Missing an enchanter? Get a bard. Missing a secondary tank? Get a bard.  Can't afford the extortion folks are charging for KEI? Get a bard.  Missing a shaman? Get a bard.  Bards are like that BASF Corporation.  We don't make the group - we make the group better.<br>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
