	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Wed, Apr 30th 10:21 AM 2003</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Good<span id=notbold>[3.65]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>You didn't mention your level. Looks like you have pretty good gear.&nbsp;&nbsp;But I do not PvP.  What I have read about PvP bards would indicate that you would be more interested in ranged work using songs than in melee (depending on yor victim).  Your MR is pretty good but your PR and DR are low. Watch out for shaman!  With scores like that they can eat you with DOTs.<br><br>Your max damage for your primary hand can be roughly calculated using this formula:<br><br>((Weapon DMG Rating+1) * 2)+(Your Level-25)/3+(STR-100)/5 rounding down.  The off hand formula is the same but without the STR calculation.<br><br>Best way to increase damage output is to increase haste or get a weapon with a better damage/dly ratio.<br><br>As a bard your best bet is to find a good combination of songs and melee that will increase your total damage output over time.  Bard's, I hear, can be nasty in PvP if played well.  Most folks I know that PvP are genuinly scared of PvPing a bard in the open (in a dungeon or confined area is a different matter).<br><br>My 2 cents. Not sure how much it's worth to you though.<br>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 >&nbsp;</td><td align=right valign=bottom>
	   <span style='font-weight: normal; font-size: 9px;'>[<a href=#top>Top</a>]</span></tr>
