	   <form action=http://www1.allakhazam.com/perl/strategy/mrate.pl name=f105129329616015><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=4&mid=105129329616015>Song twisting</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=4&mid=105129329616015#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=48595><span id= >yoconnor</span></a>, <span id= > </span><br><span id=notbold>23 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Fri, Apr 25th 2:33 PM 2003</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent<span id=notbold>[2.96]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>I just wanted to point out that you can twist 4 songs on a regular basis.&nbsp;&nbsp;Each song has a 3 second cast time.  If a song drops at all, it will only be for a second or less.  It is possible to twist 5 songs, but the 5th song either needs to be an instant cast song like the click from Breath of Harmony, or it has to be a duration song like amplification or battlecry of vah shir.  During a 5 song twist your 5th duration song will drop for about 3-6 seconds depending on the duration of the song, every other twist, and 1 other song in the twist will drop as well.  BUT...  it is possible to have a 5 song twist going with only 1 song dropping for a short duration.  That is the real deal on how many songs you can play... <br>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 >&nbsp;</td><td align=right valign=bottom>
